  "prompt_text": "Design an end-of-life care planning tool. Address both the medical decision-making and the existential questions it raises.",
  "response_text": "**End-of-Life Care Planning Tool: \"Life's Journey Map\"**\n\n**Medical Decision-Making Component:**\n\n1.  **Medical History and Goals**:\n    - Create a comprehensive medical history, including:\n        - Chronic conditions\n        - Current medications\n        - Allergies\n        - Previous surgeries or hospitalizations\n    - Identify patient's medical goals and priorities:\n        - What are the patient's main health concerns?\n        - What is the patient's quality of life?\n        - Are there any specific treatments or interventions the patient wishes to pursue or avoid?\n\n2.  **Medical Decision-Making Preferences**:\n    - Create a medical advance directive (living will):\n        - Specify the patient's preferences for life-sustaining treatments (e.g., CPR, ventilator support)\n        - Identify the patient's wishes regarding pain management and symptom relief\n        - Designate a healthcare proxy or decision-maker\n    - Discuss and document the patient's values and preferences regarding medical treatment:\n        - What is the patient's attitude toward risk and uncertainty?\n        - Are there any cultural or spiritual considerations that impact medical decision-making?\n\n**Existential Questions and Planning Component:**\n\n1.  **Personal Values and Legacy**:\n    - Explore the patient's personal values, goals, and priorities:\n        - What gives the patient's life meaning and purpose?\n        - Are there any unresolved issues or regrets?\n        - What kind of legacy does the patient want to leave behind?\n    - Discuss and document the patient's wishes regarding:\n        - Funeral or memorial services\n        - Organ donation\n        - Donating body to science or medical education\n\n2.  **Relationships and Support Network**:\n    - Identify the patient's support network:\n        - Family members and friends\n        - Caregivers and healthcare providers\n    - Discuss and document the patient's wishes regarding:\n        - Visitation and communication during hospitalization or end-of-life care\n        - Involvement in decision-making and care planning\n\n3.  **Personal and Spiritual Well-being**:\n    - Explore the patient's spiritual and emotional needs:\n        - Are there any spiritual or faith-based practices that provide comfort?\n        - Are there any unresolved emotional issues or conflicts?\n    - Discuss and document the patient's wishes regarding:\n        - Spiritual support and care\n        - Emotional support and counseling\n\n**Implementation and Review:**\n\n- Regularly review and update the Life's Journey Map to ensure accuracy and relevance.\n- Share the document with healthcare providers, family members, and caregivers to ensure everyone is informed and aligned with the patient's wishes.\n- Consider creating a digital copy of the Life's Journey Map for easy access and sharing.\n\n**Life's Journey Map Template:**\n\nCreate a comprehensive, easy-to-use template that includes the following sections:\n\n- Medical History and Goals\n- Medical Decision-Making Preferences\n- Personal Values and Legacy\n- Relationships and Support Network\n- Personal and Spiritual Well-being\n-",
